7	7	Ditch the Gold Standard: Re-evaluating Conversational Question Answering	Conversational question answering aims to provide natural-language answers to users in information-seeking conversations. Existing conversational QA benchmarks compare models with pre-collected human-human conversations, using ground-truth answers provided in conversational history. It remains unclear whether we can rely on this static evaluation for model development and whether current systems can well generalize to real-world human-machine conversations. In this work, we conduct the first large-scale human evaluation of state-of-the-art conversational QA systems, where human evaluators converse with models and judge the correctness of their answers. We find that the distribution of human machine conversations differs drastically from that of human-human conversations, and there is a disagreement between human and gold-history evaluation in terms of model ranking. We further investigate how to improve automatic evaluations, and propose a question rewriting mechanism based on predicted history, which better correlates with human judgments. Finally, we analyze the impact of various modeling strategies and discuss future directions towards building better conversational question answering systems.	10.18653/v1/2022.acl-long.555	https://aclanthology.org/2022.acl-long.555.pdf	True	2022.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Huihan', 'last': 'Li'}, {'first': 'Tianyu', 'last': 'Gao'}, {'first': 'Manan', 'last': 'Goenka'}, {'first': 'Danqi', 'last': 'Chen'}]	¿Qé alternativas proponen los autores para evaluar automáticamente sistemas de diálogo?	Iker/Llama-3-Instruct-Neurona-8b-v2	k50_p0.95_t0.2	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Ditch the Gold Standard: Re-evaluating Conversational Question Answering"" escrito por Li,Huihan et al., ¿qé alternativas proponen los autores para evaluar automáticamente sistemas de diálogo?"	"En el artículo ""Ditch the Gold Standard: Re-evaluating Conversational Question Answering"", Li, Huihan et al. proponen usar un enfoque basado en el conjunto de habilidades en lugar del conjunto de oro para evaluar automáticamente sistemas de diálogo. El conjunto de habilidades es un conjunto de tareas específicas que un sistema de diálogo debería ser capaz de realizar, y los autores argumentan que este enfoque proporciona una evaluación más precisa y completa de los sistemas de diálogo en comparación con el uso del conjunto de oro."	"['En', 'Ġel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġ""', 'D', 'itch', 'Ġthe', 'ĠGold', 'ĠStandard', ':', 'ĠRe', '-e', 'valu', 'ating', 'ĠConvers', 'ational', 'ĠQuestion', 'ĠAnswer', 'ing', '"",', 'ĠLi', ',', 'ĠH', 'ui', 'han', 'Ġet', 'Ġal', '.', 'Ġpro', 'pon', 'en', 'Ġusar', 'Ġun', 'Ġen', 'fo', 'que', 'Ġbas', 'ado', 'Ġen', 'Ġel', 'Ġconjunto', 'Ġde', 'Ġhabil', 'idades', 'Ġen', 'Ġlugar', 'Ġdel', 'Ġconjunto', 'Ġde', 'Ġoro', 'Ġpara', 'Ġeval', 'uar', 'ĠautomÃ¡ticamente', 'Ġsistemas', 'Ġde', 'Ġdi', 'Ã¡', 'logo', '.', 'ĠEl', 'Ġconjunto', 'Ġde', 'Ġhabil', 'idades', 'Ġes', 'Ġun', 'Ġconjunto', 'Ġde', 'Ġt', 'areas', 'ĠespecÃŃf', 'icas', 'Ġque', 'Ġun', 'Ġsistema', 'Ġde', 'Ġdi', 'Ã¡', 'logo', 'Ġdeber', 'ÃŃa', 'Ġser', 'Ġcap', 'az', 'Ġde', 'Ġrealizar', ',', 'Ġy', 'Ġlos', 'Ġauto', 'res', 'Ġargument', 'an', 'Ġque', 'Ġeste', 'Ġen', 'fo', 'que', 'Ġproporcion', 'a', 'Ġuna', 'Ġevalu', 'aciÃ³n', 'ĠmÃ¡s', 'Ġprecisa', 'Ġy', 'Ġcompleta', 'Ġde', 'Ġlos', 'Ġsistemas', 'Ġde', 'Ġdi', 'Ã¡', 'logo', 'Ġen', 'Ġcompar', 'aciÃ³n', 'Ġcon', 'Ġel', 'Ġuso', 'Ġdel', 'Ġconjunto', 'Ġde', 'Ġoro', '.', '<|eot_id|>']"	[24.274742126464844, 25.08197784423828, 24.22440528869629, 23.565279006958008, 22.78907585144043, 30.956867218017578, 25.965423583984375, 28.785030364990234, 30.00030517578125, 26.342754364013672, 27.871362686157227, 27.57296371459961, 34.581932067871094, 35.1053581237793, 29.132795333862305, 33.55189895629883, 26.48263168334961, 27.534320831298828, 28.947986602783203, 24.54243278503418, 22.69961929321289, 23.731685638427734, 24.689281463623047, 26.608579635620117, 31.97254180908203,