24	24	How-to Guides for Specific Audiences: A Corpus and Initial Findings	Instructional texts for specific target groups should ideally take into account the prior knowledge and needs of the readers in order to guide them efficiently to their desired goals. However, targeting specific groups also carries the risk of reflecting disparate social norms and subtle stereotypes. In this paper, we investigate the extent to which how-to guides from one particular platform, wikiHow, differ in practice depending on the intended audience. We conduct two case studies in which we examine qualitative features of texts written for specific audiences. In a generalization study, we investigate which differences can also be systematically demonstrated using computational methods. The results of our studies show that guides from wikiHow, like other text genres, are subject to subtle biases. We aim to raise awareness of these inequalities as a first step to addressing them in future work.	10.18653/v1/2023.acl-srw.46	https://aclanthology.org/2023.acl-srw.46.pdf	True	2023.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Nicola', 'last': 'Fanton'}, {'first': 'Agnieszka', 'last': 'Falenska'}, {'first': 'Michael', 'last': 'Roth'}]	¿Puedes resumir la configuración experimental de la sección 6.2?	Iker/Llama-3-Instruct-Neurona-8b-v2	k50_p0.95_t0.2	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""How-to Guides for Specific Audiences: A Corpus and Initial Findings"" escrito por Fanton,Nicola et al., ¿puedes resumir la configuración experimental de la sección 6.2? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: Instructional texts for specific target groups should ideally take into account the prior knowledge and needs of the readers in order to guide them efficiently to their desired goals. H"	"En la sección 6.2 del artículo ""How-to Guides for Specific Audiences: A Corpus and Initial Findings"" de Fanton, Nicola et al., la configuración experimental implica analizar cómo los textos instruccionales adaptados a grupos específicos de lectores pueden mejorar la eficiencia de los objetivos de aprendizaje. La sección se enfoca en examinar la efectividad de los textos instruccionales que consideran el conocimiento previo y las necesidades de los lectores, con el objetivo de guiarlos de manera más efectiva hacia sus objetivos deseados."	"['En', 'Ġla', 'Ġse', 'cciÃ³n', 'Ġ', '6', '.', '2', 'Ġdel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġ""', 'How', '-to', 'ĠGuides', 'Ġfor', 'ĠSpecific', 'ĠAud', 'iences', ':', 'ĠA', 'ĠCorpus', 'Ġand', 'ĠInitial', 'ĠFind', 'ings', '""', 'Ġde', 'ĠFant', 'on', ',', 'ĠNicola', 'Ġet', 'Ġal', '.,', 'Ġla', 'Ġconfigur', 'aciÃ³n', 'Ġexperimental', 'Ġimp', 'lica', 'Ġanal', 'izar', 'ĠcÃ³mo', 'Ġlos', 'Ġtext', 'os', 'Ġinstr', 'u', 'ccion', 'ales', 'Ġadapt', 'ados', 'Ġa', 'Ġgrupos', 'ĠespecÃŃf', 'icos', 'Ġde', 'Ġlect', 'ores', 'Ġpueden', 'Ġmejorar', 'Ġla', 'Ġef', 'ici', 'encia', 'Ġde', 'Ġlos', 'Ġobjet', 'ivos', 'Ġde', 'Ġaprend', 'iz', 'aje', '.', 'ĠLa', 'Ġse', 'cciÃ³n', 'Ġse', 'Ġenf', 'oca', 'Ġen', 'Ġexam', 'inar', 'Ġla', 'Ġefect', 'ividad', 'Ġde', 'Ġlos', 'Ġtext', 'os', 'Ġinstr', 'u', 'ccion', 'ales', 'Ġque', 'Ġconsider', 'an', 'Ġel', 'Ġconoc', 'imiento', 'Ġprev', 'io', 'Ġy', 'Ġlas', 'Ġneces', 'idades', 'Ġde', 'Ġlos', 'Ġlect', 'ores', ',', 'Ġcon', 'Ġel', 'Ġobjetivo', 'Ġde', 'Ġgu', 'iar', 'los', 'Ġde', 'Ġmanera', 'ĠmÃ¡s', 'Ġefect', 'iva', 'Ġhacia', 'Ġsus', 'Ġobjet', 'ivos', 'Ġdes', 'ead', 'os', '.', '<|eot_id|>']"	[20.076011657714844, 22.860084533691406, 23.071327209472656, 30.453399658203125, 25.641496658325195, 31.286970138549805, 28.262907028198242, 28.089813232421875, 24.773117065429688, 24.869184494018555, 23.937528610229492, 22.0385684967041, 31.206634521484375, 28.594881057739258, 28.593708038330078, 28.56757926940918, 27.304031372070312, 24.096281051635742, 28.43818473815918, 28.859050750732422, 29.864355087280273, 28.657665252685547, 27.946727752685547, 29.42118263244629, 33.67546463012695, 29.485706329345703, 23.81565284729004, 24.938243865966797, 31.47784423828125, 26.921276092529297,