40	40	Multi-Source Neural Machine Translation with Data Augmentation	Multi-source translation systems translate from multiple languages to a single target language. By using information from these multiple sources, these systems achieve large gains in accuracy. To train these systems, it is necessary to have corpora with parallel text in multiple sources and the target language. However, these corpora are rarely complete in practice due to the difficulty of providing human translations in all of the relevant languages. In this paper, we propose a data augmentation approach to fill such incomplete parts using multi-source neural machine translation (NMT). In our experiments, results varied over different language combinations but significant gains were observed when using a source language similar to the target language.		https://aclanthology.org/2018.iwslt-1.7.pdf	True	2018.iwslt.xml	[{'first': 'Yuta', 'last': 'Nishimura'}, {'first': 'Katsuhito', 'last': 'Sudoh'}, {'first': 'Graham', 'last': 'Neubig'}, {'first': 'Satoshi', 'last': 'Nakamura'}]	¿Qué tipos de expansión artificial de datos usan los autores?	Iker/Llama-3-Instruct-Neurona-8b-v2	default	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Multi-Source Neural Machine Translation with Data Augmentation"" escrito por Nishimura,Yuta et al., ¿qué tipos de expansión artificial de datos usan los autores?"	"En el artículo titulado ""Multi-Source Neural Machine Translation with Data Augmentation"" escrito por Nishimura, Yuta et al., los autores utilizan la expansión artificial de datos mediante la técnica de ""back-translation"". Esta técnica implica crear nuevos ejemplos de entrenamiento al traducir de vuelta frases en una lengua al idioma objetivo y luego añadir estas frases traducidas de vuelta a los datos de entrenamiento originales."	"['En', 'Ġel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġtit', 'ulado', 'Ġ""', 'Multi', '-', 'Source', 'ĠNeural', 'ĠMachine', 'ĠTranslation', 'Ġwith', 'ĠData', 'ĠAug', 'mentation', '""', 'Ġesc', 'rito', 'Ġpor', 'ĠN', 'ish'