47	47	Ditch the Gold Standard: Re-evaluating Conversational Question Answering	Conversational question answering aims to provide natural-language answers to users in information-seeking conversations. Existing conversational QA benchmarks compare models with pre-collected human-human conversations, using ground-truth answers provided in conversational history. It remains unclear whether we can rely on this static evaluation for model development and whether current systems can well generalize to real-world human-machine conversations. In this work, we conduct the first large-scale human evaluation of state-of-the-art conversational QA systems, where human evaluators converse with models and judge the correctness of their answers. We find that the distribution of human machine conversations differs drastically from that of human-human conversations, and there is a disagreement between human and gold-history evaluation in terms of model ranking. We further investigate how to improve automatic evaluations, and propose a question rewriting mechanism based on predicted history, which better correlates with human judgments. Finally, we analyze the impact of various modeling strategies and discuss future directions towards building better conversational question answering systems.	10.18653/v1/2022.acl-long.555	https://aclanthology.org/2022.acl-long.555.pdf	True	2022.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Huihan', 'last': 'Li'}, {'first': 'Tianyu', 'last': 'Gao'}, {'first': 'Manan', 'last': 'Goenka'}, {'first': 'Danqi', 'last': 'Chen'}]	¿Qé alternativas proponen los autores para evaluar automáticamente sistemas de diálogo?	Iker/Llama-3-Instruct-Neurona-8b-v2	default	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Ditch the Gold Standard: Re-evaluating Conversational Question Answering"" escrito por Li,Huihan et al., ¿qé alternativas proponen los autores para evaluar automáticamente sistemas de diálogo?"	"En el artículo ""Ditch the Gold Standard: Re-evaluating Conversational Question Answering"", Li, Huihan et al. proponen usar el ""F1 score"" como una alternativa para evaluar automáticamente sistemas de diálogo. El F1 score es una métrica que combina tanto la precisión como la recuperación, proporcionando una medida más balanceada de la efectividad de un sistema en comparación con usar el Gold Standard, que puede ser sesgado y no representativo de la complejidad real de las interacciones humanas."	"['En', 'Ġel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġ""', 'D', 'itch', 'Ġthe', 'ĠGold', 'ĠStandard', ':', 'ĠRe', '-e', 'valu', 'ating', 'ĠConvers', 'ational', 'ĠQuestion', 'ĠAnswer', 'ing', '"",', 'ĠLi', ',', 'ĠH', 'ui', 'han', 'Ġet', 'Ġal', '.', 'Ġpro', 'pon', 'en', 'Ġusar', 'Ġel', 'Ġ""', 'F', '1', 'Ġscore', '""', 'Ġcomo', 'Ġuna', 'Ġaltern', 'ativa', 'Ġpara', 'Ġeval', 'uar', 'ĠautomÃ¡ticamente', 'Ġsistemas', 'Ġde', 'Ġdi', 'Ã¡', 'logo', '.', 'ĠEl', 'ĠF', '1', 'Ġscore', 'Ġes', 'Ġuna', 'ĠmÃ©', 'tr', 'ica', 'Ġque', 'Ġcomb', 'ina', 'Ġtanto', 'Ġla', 'Ġprecis', 'iÃ³n', 'Ġcomo', 'Ġla', 'Ġrecuper', 'aciÃ³n', ',', 'Ġproporcion', 'ando', 'Ġuna', 'Ġmedida', 'ĠmÃ¡s', 'Ġbalance', 'ada', 'Ġde', 'Ġla', 'Ġefect', 'ividad', 'Ġde', 'Ġun', 'Ġsistema', 'Ġen', 'Ġcompar', 'aciÃ³n', 'Ġcon', 'Ġusar', 'Ġel', 'ĠGold', 'ĠStandard', ',', 'Ġque', 'Ġpuede', 'Ġser', 'Ġses', 'gado', 'Ġy', 'Ġno', 'Ġrepresent', 'ativo', 'Ġde', 'Ġla', 'Ġcomple', 'j', 'idad', 'Ġreal', 'Ġde', 'Ġlas', 'Ġinter', 'acciones', 'Ġhuman', 'as', '.', '<|eot_id|>']"	[24.274742126464844, 25.08197784423828, 24.22440528869629, 23.565279006958008, 22.78907585144043, 30.956867218017578, 25.965423583984375, 28.785030364990234, 30.00030517578125, 26.342754364013672, 27.871362686157227, 27.57296371459961, 34.581932067871094, 35.1053581237793, 29.132795333862305, 33.55189895629883, 26.48263168334961, 27.534320831298828, 28.947986602783203, 24.54243278503418, 22.69961929321289, 23.731685638427734, 24.689281463623047, 26.608579635620117, 31.97254180908203, 23.092967987060547, 28.108600616455078, 26.451984405517578, 22.36793327331543, 32.8494987487793, 27.044408798217