60	60	Multi-Source Neural Machine Translation with Data Augmentation	Multi-source translation systems translate from multiple languages to a single target language. By using information from these multiple sources, these systems achieve large gains in accuracy. To train these systems, it is necessary to have corpora with parallel text in multiple sources and the target language. However, these corpora are rarely complete in practice due to the difficulty of providing human translations in all of the relevant languages. In this paper, we propose a data augmentation approach to fill such incomplete parts using multi-source neural machine translation (NMT). In our experiments, results varied over different language combinations but significant gains were observed when using a source language similar to the target language.		https://aclanthology.org/2018.iwslt-1.7.pdf	True	2018.iwslt.xml	[{'first': 'Yuta', 'last': 'Nishimura'}, {'first': 'Katsuhito', 'last': 'Sudoh'}, {'first': 'Graham', 'last': 'Neubig'}, {'first': 'Satoshi', 'last': 'Nakamura'}]	¿Qué tipos de expansión artificial de datos usan los autores?	Iker/Llama-3-Instruct-Neurona-8b-v2	default	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Multi-Source Neural Machine Translation with Data Augmentation"" escrito por Nishimura,Yuta et al., ¿qué tipos de expansión artificial de datos usan los autores? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: Multi-source translation systems translate from multiple languages to a single target language. By using information from these multiple sources, these systems achieve large gains in ac"	"En el artículo ""Multi-Source Neural Machine Translation with Data Augmentation"" de Nishimura, Yuta et al., los autores utilizan la ampliación de datos mediante la técnica de ""Back-Translation"" como su método de expansión artificial de datos. Esta técnica implica generar frases en el idioma fuente aplicando una traducción inversa a las frases en el idioma objetivo, creando así nuevos ejemplos de entrenamiento para el modelo de traducción automática."	"['En', 'Ġel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġ""', 'Multi', '-', 'Source', 'ĠNeural', 'ĠMachine', 'ĠTranslation', 'Ġwith', 'ĠData', 'ĠAug', 'mentation', '""', 'Ġde', 'ĠN', 'ish', 'im', 'ura', ',', 'ĠY', 'uta', 'Ġet', 'Ġal', '.,', 'Ġlos', 'Ġauto', 'res', 'Ġutiliz', 'an', 'Ġla', 'Ġampl', 'i', 'aciÃ³n', 'Ġde', 'Ġdatos', 'Ġmediante', 'Ġla', 'ĠtÃ©cn', 'ica', 'Ġde', 'Ġ""', 'Back', '-', 'Translation', '""', 'Ġcomo', 'Ġsu', 'ĠmÃ©todo', 'Ġde', 'Ġexpans', 'iÃ³n', 'Ġartificial', 'Ġde', 'Ġdatos', '.', 'ĠEsta', 'ĠtÃ©cn', 'ica', 'Ġimp', 'lica', 'Ġgenerar', 'Ġfr', 'ases', 'Ġen', 'Ġel', 'Ġidi', 'oma', 'Ġfu', 'ente', 'Ġaplic', 'ando', 'Ġuna', 'Ġtrad', 'ucciÃ³n', 'Ġinvers', 'a', 'Ġa', 'Ġlas', 'Ġfr', 'ases', 'Ġen', 'Ġel', 'Ġidi', 'oma', 'Ġobjetivo', ',', 'Ġcre', 'ando', 'ĠasÃŃ', 'Ġnuevos', 'Ġej', 'emp', 'los', 'Ġde', 'Ġentren', 'amiento', 'Ġpara', 'Ġel', 'Ġmodelo', 'Ġde', 'Ġtrad', 'ucciÃ³n', 'Ġautom', 'Ã¡tica', '.', '<|eot_id|>']"	[18.812599182128906, 24.143047332763672, 24.349853515625, 23.533456802368164, 24.98116111755371, 28.355449676513672, 27.622236251831055, 26.119253158569336, 26.736082077026367, 26.646507263183594, 26.542789459228516, 26.703845977783203, 28.003890991210938, 29.192716598510742, 26.14503288269043, 22.53692054748535, 23.860403060913086, 27.669506072998047, 30.65414810180664, 36.345890045166016, 26.197731018066406, 26.502304077148438, 27.33013916015625, 23.835643768310547, 27.30255889892578, 27.295875549316406, 25.236011505126953, 26.553524017333984, 30.56201171875, 25.10329818725586, 33.67677307128906, 19.478567123413086, 19.54824447631836, 32.115291595458984, 27.87483024597168, 24.421220779418945, 25.631935119628906, 17.357696533203125, 17.96750831604004, 15.623574256896973, 33.08856964111328, 21.31174087524414, 15.039990425109863, 15.213974952697754, 22.955278396606445, 25.427749633789062, 21.339588165283203, 22.28480339050293, 19.286149978637695, 21.452491760253906, 25.497148513793945, 23.413551330566