71	71	MultiPICo: Multilingual Perspectivist Irony Corpus	Recently, several scholars have contributed to the growth of a new theoretical framework in NLP called perspectivism. This approach aimsto leverage data annotated by different individuals to model diverse perspectives that affect their opinions on subjective phenomena such as irony. In this context, we propose MultiPICo, a multilingual perspectivist corpus of ironic short conversations in different languages andlinguistic varieties extracted from Twitter and Reddit. The corpus includes sociodemographic information about its annotators. Our analysis of the annotated corpus shows how different demographic cohorts may significantly disagree on their annotation of irony and how certain cultural factors influence the perception of the phenomenon and the agreement on the annotation. Moreover, we show how disaggregated annotations and rich annotator metadata can be exploited to benchmark the ability of large language models to recognize irony, their positionality with respect to sociodemographic groups, and the efficacy of perspective-taking prompting for irony detection in multiple languages.	10.18653/v1/2024.acl-long.849	https://aclanthology.org/2024.acl-long.849.pdf	True	2024.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Silvia', 'last': 'Casola'}, {'first': 'Simona', 'last': 'Frenda'}, {'first': 'Soda Marem', 'last': 'Lo'}, {'first': 'Erhan', 'last': 'Sezerer'}, {'first': 'Antonio', 'last': 'Uva'}, {'first': 'Valerio', 'last': 'Basile'}, {'first': 'Cristina', 'last': 'Bosco'}, {'first': 'Alessandro', 'last': 'Pedrani'}, {'first': 'Chiara', 'last': 'Rubagotti'}, {'first': 'Viviana', 'last': 'Patti'}, {'first': 'Davide', 'last': 'Bernardi'}]	¿Por qué es necesario incluir el context sociodemografico de los anotadores en el corpus?	Iker/Llama-3-Instruct-Neurona-8b-v2	default	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""MultiPICo: Multilingual Perspectivist Irony Corpus"" escrito por Casola,Silvia et al., ¿por qué es necesario incluir el context sociodemografico de los anotadores en el corpus? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: Recently, several scholars have contributed to the growth of a new theoretical framework in NLP called perspectivism. This approach aimsto leverage data annotated by different individua"	s con different perspectives and backgrounds to improve the performance of natural language processing models. However, the impact of the sociodemographic context of the annotators on the quality and reliability of the annotated data has not been fully explored. In the MultiPICo project, we aim to address this gap by creating a multilingual corpus of annotated data that includes information about the sociodemographic context of the annotators. This corpus will allow researchers to study the effect of the annotators' background on the quality of the annotated data and to develop more robust and accurate NLP models.	"['s', 'Ġcon', 'Ġdifferent', 'Ġperspectives', 'Ġand', 'Ġbackgrounds', 'Ġto', 'Ġimprove', 'Ġthe', 'Ġperformance', 'Ġof', 'Ġnatural', 'Ġlanguage', 'Ġprocessing', 'Ġmodels', '.', 'ĠHowever', ',', 'Ġthe', 'Ġimpact', 'Ġof', 'Ġthe', 'Ġsoci', 'odem', 'ographic', 'Ġcontext', 'Ġof', 'Ġthe', 'Ġannot', 'ators', 'Ġon', 'Ġthe', 'Ġquality', 'Ġand', 'Ġreliability', 'Ġof', 'Ġthe', 'Ġannotated', 'Ġdata', 'Ġhas', 'Ġnot', 'Ġbeen', 'Ġfully', 'Ġexplored', '.', 'ĠIn', 'Ġthe', 'ĠMulti', 'PIC', 'o', 'Ġproject', ',', 'Ġwe', 'Ġaim', 'Ġto', 'Ġaddress', 'Ġthis', 'Ġgap', 'Ġby', 'Ġcreating', 'Ġa', 'Ġmult', 'ilingual', 'Ġcorpus', 'Ġof', 'Ġannotated', 'Ġdata', 'Ġthat', 'Ġincludes', 'Ġinformation', 'Ġabout', 'Ġthe', 'Ġsoci', 'odem', 'ographic', 'Ġcontext', 'Ġof', 'Ġthe', 'Ġannot', 'ators', '.', 'ĠThis', 'Ġcorpus', 'Ġwill', 'Ġallow', 'Ġresearchers', 'Ġto', 'Ġstudy', 'Ġthe', 'Ġeffect', 'Ġof', 'Ġthe', 'Ġannot', 'ators', ""'"", 'Ġbackground', 'Ġon', 'Ġthe', 'Ġquality', 'Ġof', 'Ġthe', 'Ġannotated', 'Ġdata', 'Ġand', 'Ġto', 'Ġdevelop', 'Ġmore', 'Ġrobust', 'Ġand', 'Ġaccurate', 'ĠN', 'LP', 'Ġmodels', '.', '<|