76	76	Causes and Cures for Interference in Multilingual Translation	Multilingual machine translation models can benefit from synergy between different language pairs, but also suffer from interference. While there is a growing number of sophisticated methods that aim to eliminate interference, our understanding of interference as a phenomenon is still limited. This work identifies the main factors that contribute to interference in multilingual machine translation. Through systematic experimentation, we find that interference (or synergy) are primarily determined by model size, data size, and the proportion of each language pair within the total dataset. We observe that substantial interference occurs mainly when the model is very small with respect to the available training data, and that using standard transformer configurations with less than one billion parameters largely alleviates interference and promotes synergy. Moreover, we show that tuning the sampling temperature to control the proportion of each language pair in the data is key to balancing the amount of interference between low and high resource language pairs effectively, and can lead to superior performance overall.	10.18653/v1/2023.acl-long.883	https://aclanthology.org/2023.acl-long.883.pdf	True	2023.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Uri', 'last': 'Shaham'}, {'first': 'Maha', 'last': 'Elbayad'}, {'first': 'Vedanuj', 'last': 'Goswami'}, {'first': 'Omer', 'last': 'Levy'}, {'first': 'Shruti', 'last': 'Bhosale'}]	¿Qué solucion proponen los autores para aminorar el problema de interferencia observado en modelos multilingües de traducción automática?	Iker/Llama-3-Instruct-Neurona-8b-v2	default	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Causes and Cures for Interference in Multilingual Translation"" escrito por Shaham,Uri et al., ¿qué solucion proponen los autores para aminorar el problema de interferencia observado en modelos multilingües de traducción automática? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: Multilingual machine translation models can benefit from synergy between different language pairs, but also suffer from interference. While there is a growing number of sophisticated me"	"En el artículo titulado ""Causes and Cures for Interference in Multilingual Translation"" escrito por Shaham,Uri et al., los autores proponen un método llamado ""Multilingual Denoising Autoencoder"" (MDE) para reducir el problema de interferencia observado en modelos multilingües de traducción automática. MDE funciona aprendiendo una representación comprimida de las fuentes que es invariante a la interferencia, lo que ayuda a reducir su impacto en la traducción."	"['En', 'Ġel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġtit', 'ulado', 'Ġ""', 'Ca', 'uses', 'Ġand', 'ĠC', 'ures', 'Ġfor', 'ĠInter', 'ference', 'Ġin', 'ĠMult', 'ilingual', 'ĠTranslation', '""', 'Ġesc', 'rito', 'Ġpor', 'ĠShah', 'am', ',', 'Uri', 'Ġet', 'Ġal', '.,', 'Ġlos', 'Ġauto', 'res', 'Ġpro', 'pon', 'en', 'Ġun', 'ĠmÃ©todo', 'Ġllam', 'ado', 'Ġ""', 'Mult', 'ilingual', 'ĠDen', 'o', 'ising', 'ĠAuto', 'encoder', '""', 'Ġ(', 'M', 'DE', ')', 'Ġpara', 'Ġredu', 'cir', 'Ġel', 'Ġproblema', 'Ġde', 'Ġinterfer', 'encia', 'Ġobserv', 'ado', 'Ġen', 'Ġmodelos', 'Ġmult', 'iling', 'Ã¼', 'es', 'Ġde', 'Ġtrad', 'ucciÃ³n', 'Ġautom', 'Ã¡tica', '.', 'ĠM', 'DE', 'Ġfunciona', 'Ġaprend', 'iendo', 'Ġuna', 'Ġrepresent', 'aciÃ³n', 'Ġcompr', 'im', 'ida', 'Ġde', 'Ġlas', 'Ġf', 'uentes', 'Ġque', 'Ġes', 'Ġin', 'vari', 'ante', 'Ġa', 'Ġla', 'Ġinterfer', 'encia', ',', 'Ġlo', 'Ġque', 'Ġayuda', 'Ġa', 'Ġredu', 'cir', 'Ġsu', 'Ġimpact', 'o', 'Ġen', 'Ġla', 'Ġtrad', 'ucciÃ³n', '.', '<|eot_id|>']"	[17.611967086791992, 23.08584976196289, 23.26723289489746, 22.619770050048828, 32.12796401977539, 25.552654266357422, 23.183244705200195, 26.281009674072266, 27.32150650024414, 26.577816009521484, 31.251115798950195, 27.296640396118164, 26.20132064819336, 29.23078727722168, 27.087764739990234, 28.830476760864258, 34.188114166259766, 27.046955108642578, 25.354625701904297, 21.768917083740234, 31.26