88	88	Let’s Go Real Talk: Spoken Dialogue Model for Face-to-Face Conversation	In this paper, we introduce a novel Face-to-Face spoken dialogue model. It processes audio-visual speech from user input and generates audio-visual speech as the response, marking the initial step towards creating an avatar chatbot system without relying on intermediate text. To this end, we newly introduce MultiDialog, the first large-scale multimodal (i.e, audio and visual) spoken dialogue corpus containing 340 hours of approximately 9,000 dialogues, recorded based on the open domain dialogue dataset, TopicalChat. The MultiDialog contains parallel audio-visual recordings of conversation partners acting according to the given script with emotion annotations, which we expect to open up research opportunities in multimodal synthesis. Our Face-to-Face spoken dialogue model incorporates a textually pretrained large language model and adapts it into the audio-visual spoken dialogue domain by incorporating speech-text joint pretraining. Through extensive experiments, we validate the effectiveness of our model in facilitating a face-to-face conversation. Demo and data are available at https://multidialog.github.io and https://huggingface.co/datasets/IVLLab/MultiDialog, respectively.	10.18653/v1/2024.acl-long.860	https://aclanthology.org/2024.acl-long.860.pdf	True	2024.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Se', 'last': 'Park'}, {'first': 'Chae', 'last': 'Kim'}, {'first': 'Hyeongseop', 'last': 'Rha'}, {'first': 'Minsu', 'last': 'Kim'}, {'first': 'Joanna', 'last': 'Hong'}, {'first': 'Jeonghun', 'last': 'Yeo'}, {'first': 'Yong', 'last': 'Ro'}]	¿Por qué los autores no usan las etiquetas de emociones que contiene el dataset que crearon?	Iker/Llama-3-Instruct-Neurona-8b-v2	k50_p0.90_t0.1	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Let’s Go Real Talk: Spoken Dialogue Model for Face-to-Face Conversation"" escrito por Park,Se et al., ¿por qué los autores no usan las etiquetas de emociones que contiene el dataset que crearon?"	"Para