104	104	How-to Guides for Specific Audiences: A Corpus and Initial Findings	Instructional texts for specific target groups should ideally take into account the prior knowledge and needs of the readers in order to guide them efficiently to their desired goals. However, targeting specific groups also carries the risk of reflecting disparate social norms and subtle stereotypes. In this paper, we investigate the extent to which how-to guides from one particular platform, wikiHow, differ in practice depending on the intended audience. We conduct two case studies in which we examine qualitative features of texts written for specific audiences. In a generalization study, we investigate which differences can also be systematically demonstrated using computational methods. The results of our studies show that guides from wikiHow, like other text genres, are subject to subtle biases. We aim to raise awareness of these inequalities as a first step to addressing them in future work.	10.18653/v1/2023.acl-srw.46	https://aclanthology.org/2023.acl-srw.46.pdf	True	2023.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Nicola', 'last': 'Fanton'}, {'first': 'Agnieszka', 'last': 'Falenska'}, {'first': 'Michael', 'last': 'Roth'}]	¿Puedes resumir la configuración experimental de la sección 6.2?	Iker/Llama-3-Instruct-Neurona-8b-v2	k50_p0.90_t0.1	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""How-to Guides for Specific Audiences: A Corpus and Initial Findings"" escrito por Fanton,Nicola et al., ¿puedes resumir la configuración experimental de la sección 6.2? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: Instructional texts for specific target groups should ideally take into account the prior knowledge and needs of the readers in order to guide them efficiently to their desired goals. H"	"En la sección 6.2 del artículo ""How-to Guides for Specific Audiences: A Corpus and Initial Findings"" de Fanton, Nicola et al., la configuración experimental implica analizar cómo los textos instruccionales adaptados a grupos objetivo específicos pueden guiar eficientemente a los lectores hacia sus objetivos deseados. Esto se logra teniendo en cuenta el conocimiento previo y las necesidades de los lectores, lo que permite una mejor comprensión y aplicación de la información proporcionada."	"['En', 'Ġla', 'Ġse', 'cciÃ³n', 'Ġ', '6', '.', '2', 'Ġdel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġ""', 'How', '-to', 'ĠGuides', 'Ġfor', 'ĠSpecific', 'ĠAud', 'iences', ':', 'ĠA', 'ĠCorpus', 'Ġand', 'ĠInitial', 'ĠFind', 'ings', '""', 'Ġde', 'ĠFant', 'on', ',', 'ĠNicola', 'Ġet', 'Ġal', '.,', 'Ġla', 'Ġconfigur', 'aciÃ³n', 'Ġexperimental', 'Ġimp', 'lica', 'Ġanal', 'izar', 'ĠcÃ³mo', 'Ġlos', 'Ġtext', 'os', 'Ġinstr', 'u', 'ccion', 'ales', 'Ġadapt', 'ados', 'Ġa', 'Ġgrupos', 'Ġobjetivo', 'ĠespecÃŃf', 'icos', 'Ġpueden', 'Ġgu', 'iar', 'Ġef', 'icient', 'emente', 'Ġa', 'Ġlos', 'Ġlect', 'ores', 'Ġhacia', 'Ġsus', 'Ġobjet', 'ivos', 'Ġdes', 'ead', 'os', '.', 'ĠEsto', 'Ġse', 'Ġlog', 'ra', 'Ġten', 'iendo', 'Ġen', 'Ġcuenta', 'Ġel', 'Ġconoc', 'imiento', 'Ġprev', 'io', 'Ġy', 'Ġlas', 'Ġneces', 'idades', 'Ġde', 'Ġlos', 'Ġlect', 'ores', ',', 'Ġlo', 'Ġque', 'Ġpermite', 'Ġuna', 'Ġmejor', 'Ġcomp', 'rens', 'iÃ³n', 'Ġy', 'ĠaplicaciÃ³n', 'Ġde', 'Ġla', 'ĠinformaciÃ³n', 'Ġproporcion', 'ada', '.', '<|eot_id|>']"	[20.076011657714844, 22.860084533691406, 23.071327209472656, 30.453399658203125, 25.641496658325195, 31.286970138549805, 28.262907028198242, 28.089813232421875, 24.773117065429688, 24.869184494018555, 23.937528610229492, 22.0385684967041, 31.206634521484375, 28.594881057739258, 28.593708038330078, 28.56757926940918, 27.304031372070312, 24.096281051635742, 28.43818473815918, 28.859050750732422, 29.864355087280273, 28.657665252685547, 27.946727752685547, 29.42118263244629, 33.67546463012695, 29.485706329345703, 23.81565284729004, 24.938243865966797, 31.47784423828125, 26.921276092529297, 24.582176208496094, 24.534589767456055, 29.268186569213867, 28.926605224609375, 22.520977020263672, 23.13982391357422, 36.922096252441406, 28.420576095581055, 21.156305