106	106	Applying the Transformer to Character-level Transduction	The transformer has been shown to outperform recurrent neural network-based sequence-to-sequence models in various word-level NLP tasks. Yet for character-level transduction tasks, e.g. morphological inflection generation and historical text normalization, there are few works that outperform recurrent models using the transformer. In an empirical study, we uncover that, in contrast to recurrent sequence-to-sequence models, the batch size plays a crucial role in the performance of the transformer on character-level tasks, and we show that with a large enough batch size, the transformer does indeed outperform recurrent models. We also introduce a simple technique to handle feature-guided character-level transduction that further improves performance. With these insights, we achieve state-of-the-art performance on morphological inflection and historical text normalization. We also show that the transformer outperforms a strong baseline on two other character-level transduction tasks: grapheme-to-phoneme conversion and transliteration.	10.18653/v1/2021.eacl-main.163	https://aclanthology.org/2021.eacl-main.163.pdf	True	2021.eacl.xml	[{'first': 'Shijie', 'last': 'Wu'}, {'first': 'Ryan', 'last': 'Cotterell'}, {'first': 'Mans', 'last': 'Hulden'}]	¿Cuáles son las cuatro tareas de transducción a nivel de caracteres que los autores consideran?	Iker/Llama-3-Instruct-Neurona-8b-v2	k50_p0.90_t0.1	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Applying the Transformer to Character-level Transduction"" escrito por Wu,Shijie et al., ¿cuáles son las cuatro tareas de transducción a nivel de caracteres que los autores consideran? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: The transformer has been shown to outperform recurrent neural network-based sequence-to-sequence models in various word-level NLP tasks. Yet for character-level transduction tasks, e.g."	"En el artículo ""Applying the Transformer to Character-level Transduction"" de Wu, Shijie et al., los autores consideran cuatro tareas de transducción a nivel de caracteres. Estas tareas son:1. Inglés a Chino (En2Zhi)2. Chino a Inglés (Zhi2En)3. Alemán a Inglés (De2En)4. Inglés a Alemán (En2De)Estas tareas implican traducir texto de un idioma a otro a nivel de caracteres, en lugar de a nivel de palabras."	"['En', 'Ġel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġ""', 'App', 'lying', 'Ġthe', 'ĠTransformer', 'Ġto', 'ĠCharacter', '-level', 'ĠTrans', 'duction', '""', 'Ġde', 'ĠWu', ',', 'ĠSh', 'ij', 'ie', 'Ġet', 'Ġal', '.,', 'Ġlos', 'Ġauto', 'res', 'Ġconsider', 'an', 'Ġcuatro', 'Ġt', 'areas', 'Ġde', 'Ġtrans', 'du', 'cciÃ³n', 'Ġa', 'Ġnivel', 'Ġde', 'Ġcaracteres', '.', 'ĠEst', 'as', 'Ġt', 'areas', 'Ġson', ':ĊĊ', '1', '.', 'ĠIn', 'gl', 'Ã©s', 'Ġa', 'ĠCh', 'ino', 'Ġ(', 'En', '2', 'Z', 'hi', ')Ċ', '2', '.', 'ĠCh', 'ino', 'Ġa', 'ĠIn', 'gl', 'Ã©s', 'Ġ(', 'Z', 'hi', '2', 'En', ')Ċ', '3', '.', 'ĠA', 'lem', 'Ã¡n', 'Ġa', 'ĠIn', 'gl', 'Ã©s', 'Ġ(', 'De', '2', 'En', ')Ċ', '4', '.', 'ĠIn', 'gl', 'Ã©s', 'Ġa', 'ĠA', 'lem', 'Ã¡n', 'Ġ(', 'En', '2', 'De', ')ĊĊ', 'Est', 'as', 'Ġt', 'areas', 'Ġimplic', 'an', 'Ġtrad', 'uc', 'ir', 'Ġtexto', 'Ġde', 'Ġun', 'Ġidi', 'oma', 'Ġa', 'Ġotro', 'Ġa', 'Ġnivel', 'Ġde', 'Ġcaracteres', ',', 'Ġen', 'Ġlugar', 'Ġde', 'Ġa', 'Ġnivel', 'Ġde', 'Ġpalabras', '.', '<|eot_id|>']"	[19.982316970825195, 25.15234375, 24.060691833496094, 23.057992935180664, 23.33749771118164, 29.916667938232422, 27.804630279541016, 29.473098754882812, 27.591115951538086, 27.35475730895996, 30.46117401123047, 28.449039459228516, 29.10818862915039, 27.478126525878906, 22.960071563720703, 23.76541519165039, 25.558147430419922, 25.611085891723633, 31.9227237701416, 31.72450065612793, 24.962656021118164, 28.473604202270508, 27.760961532592773, 25.48768424987793, 26.810964584350586, 32.36394500732422, 25.517953872680664, 33.51701736450195, 24.04216766357422, 25.07842445373535, 30.773681640625, 25.508970260620117, 24.714902877807617, 29.397537231445312, 34.82801818847656, 25.0670