119	119	Weaker Than You Think: A Critical Look at Weakly Supervised Learning	Weakly supervised learning is a popular approach for training machine learning models in low-resource settings. Instead of requesting high-quality yet costly human annotations, it allows training models with noisy annotations obtained from various weak sources. Recently, many sophisticated approaches have been proposed for robust training under label noise, reporting impressive results. In this paper, we revisit the setup of these approaches and find that the benefits brought by these approaches are significantly overestimated. Specifically, we find that the success of existing weakly supervised learning approaches heavily relies on the availability of clean validation samples which, as we show, can be leveraged much more efficiently by simply training on them. After using these clean labels in training, the advantages of using these sophisticated approaches are mostly wiped out. This remains true even when reducing the size of the available clean data to just five samples per class, making these approaches impractical. To understand the true value of weakly supervised learning, we thoroughly analyze diverse NLP datasets and tasks to ascertain when and why weakly supervised approaches work. Based on our findings, we provide recommendations for future research.	10.18653/v1/2023.acl-long.796	https://aclanthology.org/2023.acl-long.796.pdf	True	2023.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Dawei', 'last': 'Zhu'}, {'first': 'Xiaoyu', 'last': 'Shen'}, {'first': 'Marius', 'last': 'Mosbach'}, {'first': 'Andreas', 'last': 'Stephan'}, {'first': 'Dietrich', 'last': 'Klakow'}]	¿Qué enfoques de aprendizaje de maquina con supervisión débil (weakly supervised learning, WSL) comparan los autores?	Iker/Llama-3-Instruct-Neurona-8b-v2	k50_p0.90_t0.1	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Weaker Than You Think: A Critical Look at Weakly Supervised Learning"" escrito por Zhu,Dawei et al., ¿qué enfoques de aprendizaje de maquina con supervisión débil (weakly supervised learning, WSL) comparan los autores? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: Weakly supervised learning is a popular approach for training machine learning models in low-resource settings. Instead of requesting high-quality yet costly human annotations, it allow"	"En el artículo ""Weaker Than You Think: A Critical Look at Weakly Supervised Learning"" de Zhu, Dawei et al., los autores comparan varios enfoques de aprendizaje automático con supervisión débil (aprendizaje supervisado débil, WSL). Estos enfoques tienen como objetivo entrenar modelos de aprendizaje automático en entornos de baja disponibilidad de recursos sin requerir anotaciones humanas de alta calidad y costosas. El artículo analiza y discute las limitaciones y desafíos de los métodos de WSL actuales, así como sus posibles mejoras y aplicaciones futuras."	"['En', 'Ġel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġ""', 'We', 'aker', 'ĠThan', 'ĠYou', 'ĠThink', ':', 'ĠA', 'ĠCritical', 'ĠLook', 'Ġat', 'ĠWeak', 'ly', 'ĠSuperv', 'ised', 'ĠLearning', '""', 'Ġde', 'ĠZhu', ',', 'ĠDaw', 'ei', 'Ġet', 'Ġal', '.,', 'Ġlos', 'Ġauto', 'res', 'Ġcompar', 'an', 'Ġvarios', 'Ġen', 'fo', 'ques', 'Ġde', 'Ġaprend', 'iz', 'aje', 'Ġautom', 'Ã¡tico', 'Ġcon', 'Ġsuperv', 'isiÃ³n', 'ĠdÃ©', 'bil', 'Ġ(', 'ap', 'rend', 'iz', 'aje', 'Ġsuperv', 'is', 'ado', 'ĠdÃ©', 'bil', ',', 'ĠW', 'SL', ').', 'ĠEst', 'os', 'Ġen', 'fo', 'ques', 'Ġtienen', 'Ġcomo', 'Ġobjetivo', 'Ġentren', 'ar', 'Ġmodelos', 'Ġde', 'Ġaprend', 'iz', 'aje', 'Ġautom', 'Ã¡tico', 'Ġen', 'Ġent', 'orn', 'os', 'Ġde', 'Ġbaja', 'Ġdispon', 'ibilidad', 'Ġde', 'Ġrecursos', 'Ġsin', 'Ġrequer', 'ir', 'Ġan', 'ot', 'aciones', 'Ġhuman', 'as', 'Ġde', 'Ġalta', 'Ġcalidad', 'Ġy', 'Ġcost', 'osas', '.', 'ĠEl', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġanal', 'iza', 'Ġy', 'Ġdisc', 'ute', 'Ġlas', 'Ġlimit', 'aciones', 'Ġy', 'Ġdes', 'af', 'ÃŃ', 'os', 'Ġde', 'Ġlos', 'ĠmÃ©t', 'odos', 'Ġde', 'ĠW', 'SL', 'Ġact', 'uales', ',', 'ĠasÃŃ', 'Ġcomo', 'Ġsus', 'Ġpos', 'ibles', 'Ġmejor', 'as', 'Ġy', 'Ġaplic', 