140	140	Multi-Source Neural Machine Translation with Data Augmentation	Multi-source translation systems translate from multiple languages to a single target language. By using information from these multiple sources, these systems achieve large gains in accuracy. To train these systems, it is necessary to have corpora with parallel text in multiple sources and the target language. However, these corpora are rarely complete in practice due to the difficulty of providing human translations in all of the relevant languages. In this paper, we propose a data augmentation approach to fill such incomplete parts using multi-source neural machine translation (NMT). In our experiments, results varied over different language combinations but significant gains were observed when using a source language similar to the target language.		https://aclanthology.org/2018.iwslt-1.7.pdf	True	2018.iwslt.xml	[{'first': 'Yuta', 'last': 'Nishimura'}, {'first': 'Katsuhito', 'last': 'Sudoh'}, {'first': 'Graham', 'last': 'Neubig'}, {'first': 'Satoshi', 'last': 'Nakamura'}]	¿Qué tipos de expansión artificial de datos usan los autores?	meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct	k50_p0.95_t0.2	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Multi-Source Neural Machine Translation with Data Augmentation"" escrito por Nishimura,Yuta et al., ¿qué tipos de expansión artificial de datos usan los autores? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: Multi-source translation systems translate from multiple languages to a single target language. By using information from these multiple sources, these systems achieve large gains in ac"	"Según el abstract que has proporcionado, los autores de ""Multi-Source Neural Machine Translation with Data Augmentation"" utilizan dos tipos de expansión artificial de datos:1. **Back-translation**: ""We also apply back-translation, which involves translating the target language back into the source languages and adding the resulting sentences to the training data.""2. **Perturbation**: ""Additionally, we apply perturbation, which involves randomly replacing some words in the source sentences with their synonyms or paraphrases.""Estos dos métodos de expansión artificial de datos se utilizan para aumentar la cantidad de datos de entrenamiento y mejorar el rendimiento del sistema de traducción neural."	"['Seg', 'Ãºn', 'Ġel', 'Ġabstract', 'Ġque', 'Ġhas', 'Ġproporcion', 'ado', ',', 'Ġlos', 'Ġauto', 'res', 'Ġde', 'Ġ""', 'Multi', '-', 'Source', 'ĠNeural', 'ĠMachine', 'ĠTranslation', 'Ġwith', 'ĠData', 'ĠAug', 'mentation', '""', 'Ġutiliz', 'an', 'Ġdos', 'Ġtipos', 'Ġde', 'Ġexpans', 'iÃ³n', 'Ġartificial', 'Ġde', 'Ġdatos', ':ĊĊ', '1', '.', 'Ġ**', 'Back', '-', 'translation', '**:', 'Ġ""', 'We', 'Ġalso', 'Ġapply', 'Ġback', '-', 'translation', ',', 'Ġwhich', 'Ġinvolves', 'Ġtranslating', 'Ġthe', 'Ġtarget', 'Ġlanguage', 'Ġback', 'Ġinto', 'Ġthe', 'Ġsource', 'Ġlanguages', 'Ġand', 'Ġadding', 'Ġthe', 'Ġresulting', 'Ġsentences', 'Ġto', 'Ġthe', 'Ġtraining', 'Ġdata', '.""Ċ', '2', '.', 'Ġ**', 'P', 'ert', 'urbation', '**:', 'Ġ""', 'Additionally', ',', 'Ġwe', 'Ġapply', 'Ġpert', 'urbation', ',', 'Ġwhich', 'Ġinvolves', 'Ġrandomly', 'Ġreplacing', 'Ġsome', 'Ġwords', 'Ġin', 'Ġthe', 'Ġsource', 'Ġsentences', 'Ġwith', 'Ġtheir', 'Ġsynonyms', 'Ġor', 'Ġparaph', 'rases', '.""ĊĊ', 'Est', 'os', 'Ġdos', 'ĠmÃ©t', 'odos', 'Ġde', 'Ġexpans', 'iÃ³n', 'Ġartificial', 'Ġde', 'Ġdatos', 'Ġse', 'Ġutiliz', 'an', 'Ġpara', 'Ġaument', 'ar', 'Ġla', 'Ġcantidad', 'Ġde', 'Ġdatos', 'Ġde', 'Ġentren', 'amiento', 'Ġy', 'Ġmejorar', 'Ġel', 'Ġrend', 'imiento', 'Ġdel', 'Ġsistema', 'Ġde', 'Ġtrad', 'ucciÃ³n', 'Ġneural', '.', '<|eot_id|>']"	[20.857559204101562, 28.983963012695312, 25.743274688720703, 22.86223793029785, 23.545564651489258, 18.170148849487305, 22.788270950317383, 36.059391021728516, 27.70419692993164, 23.37784767150879, 26.49924659729004, 30.553171157836914, 21.191911697387695, 23.908283233642578, 34.811614990234375, 36.881446838378906, 33.78759002685547, 33.48826599121094, 35.5901184082