153	153	SCOTT: Self-Consistent Chain-of-Thought Distillation	Large language models (LMs) beyond a certain scale, demonstrate the emergent capability of generating free-text rationales for their predictions via chain-of-thought (CoT) prompting. While CoT can yield dramatically improved performance, such gains are only observed for sufficiently large LMs. Even more concerning, there is little guarantee that the generated rationales are consistent with LM’s predictions or faithfully justify the decisions. In this work, we propose SCOTT, a faithful knowledge distillation method to learn a small, self-consistent CoT model from a teacher model that is orders of magnitude larger. To form better supervision, we elicit rationales supporting the gold answers from a large LM (teacher) by contrastive decoding, which encourages the teacher to generate tokens that become more plausible only when the answer is considered. To ensure faithful distillation, we use the teacher-generated rationales to learn a student LM with a counterfactual reasoning objective, which prevents the student from ignoring the rationales to make inconsistent predictions. Experiments show that while yielding comparable performance, our method leads to a more faithful model than baselines. Further analysis shows that such a model respects the rationales more when making decisions; thus, we can improve its performance more by refining its rationales.	10.18653/v1/2023.acl-long.304	https://aclanthology.org/2023.acl-long.304.pdf	True	2023.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Peifeng', 'last': 'Wang'}, {'first': 'Zhengyang', 'last': 'Wang'}, {'first': 'Zheng', 'last': 'Li'}, {'first': 'Yifan', 'last': 'Gao'}, {'first': 'Bing', 'last': 'Yin'}, {'first': 'Xiang', 'last': 'Ren'}]	¿Cuál es el rol de la descodificación o generación contrastiva que los autores proponen?	meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct	k50_p0.95_t0.2	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""SCOTT: Self-Consistent Chain-of-Thought Distillation"" escrito por Wang,Peifeng et al., ¿cuál es el rol de la descodificación o generación contrastiva que los autores proponen? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: Large language models (LMs) beyond a certain scale, demonstrate the emergent capability of generating free-text rationales for their predictions via chain-of-thought (CoT) prompting. Wh"	"According to the abstract you provided, the authors of the paper ""SCOTT: Self-Consistent Chain-of-Thought Distillation"" propose a technique called ""contrastive generation"" or ""descodificación contrastiva"" (my translation). This technique is used to improve the quality of the generated rationales, which are the explanations for the predictions made by the large language models (LMs).In particular, the authors use a contrastive generation approach to encourage the model to generate rationales that are more diverse and relevant to the input prompt. This is achieved by training the model to generate two types of rationales: one that is similar to the original input prompt, and another that is dissimilar. The model is then trained to predict which of the two rationales is more relevant to the input prompt.The goal of this contrastive generation approach is to improve the quality of the generated rationales by encouraging the model to generate more diverse and relevant explanations for its predictions. This can help to improve the transparency and interpretability of the model's predictions, which is an important aspect of explainable AI."	"['According', 'Ġto', 'Ġthe', 'Ġabstract', 'Ġyou', 'Ġprovided', ',', 'Ġthe', 'Ġauthors', 'Ġof', 'Ġthe', 'Ġpaper', 'Ġ""', 'SC', 'OTT', ':', 'ĠSelf', '-', 'Cons', 'istent', 'ĠChain', '-of', '-Th', 'ought', 'ĠDist', 'illation', '""', 'Ġpropose', 'Ġa', 'Ġtechnique', 'Ġcalled', 'Ġ""', 'contrast', 'ive', 'Ġgeneration', '""', 'Ġor', 'Ġ""', 'desc', 'od', 'ificaciÃ³n', 'Ġcontrast', 'iva', '""', 'Ġ(', 'my', 'Ġtranslation', ').', 'ĠThis', 'Ġtechnique', 'Ġis', 'Ġused', 'Ġto', 'Ġimprove', 'Ġthe', 'Ġqua