154	154	Steering Llama 2 via Contrastive Activation Addition	We introduce Contrastive Activation Addition (CAA), a method for steering language models by modifying their activations during forward passes. CAA computes “steering vectors” by averaging the difference in residual stream activations between pairs of positive and negative examples of a particular behavior, such as factual versus hallucinatory responses. During inference, these steering vectors are added at all token positions after the user’s prompt with either a positive or negative coefficient, allowing precise control over the degree of the targeted behavior. We evaluate CAA’s effectiveness on Llama 2 Chat using multiple-choice behavioral question datasets and open-ended generation tasks. We demonstrate that CAA significantly alters model behavior, is effective over and on top of traditional methods like finetuning and system prompt design, and minimally reduces capabilities. Moreover, we gain deeper insights into CAA’s mechanisms by employing various activation space interpretation methods. CAA accurately steers model outputs and sheds light on how high-level concepts are represented in Large Language Models (LLMs).	10.18653/v1/2024.acl-long.828	https://aclanthology.org/2024.acl-long.828.pdf	True	2024.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Nina', 'last': 'Rimsky'}, {'first': 'Nick', 'last': 'Gabrieli'}, {'first': 'Julian', 'last': 'Schulz'}, {'first': 'Meg', 'last': 'Tong'}, {'first': 'Evan', 'last': 'Hubinger'}, {'first': 'Alexander', 'last': 'Turner'}]	¿Cuáles son los comportamientos del dataset de evaluación llamado 'Advanced AI Risk' de Anthropic que los autores usan?	meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct	k50_p0.95_t0.2	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Steering Llama 2 via Contrastive Activation Addition"" escrito por Rimsky,Nina et al., ¿cuáles son los comportamientos del dataset de evaluación llamado 'Advanced AI Risk' de Anthropic que los autores usan? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: We introduce Contrastive Activation Addition (CAA), a method for steering language models by modifying their activations during forward passes. CAA computes “steering vectors” by averag"	"Desafortunadamente, no puedo encontrar información sobre el artículo ""Steering Llama 2 via Contrastive Activation Addition"" escrito por Rimsky, Nina et al., ya que no es un artículo real. Es posible que sea un artículo futuro o no exista en absoluto.Sin embargo, si proporcionas más contexto o información sobre el artículo, puedo intentar ayudarte a encontrar la información que estás buscando."	"['Des', 'afort', 'un', 'adamente', ',', 'Ġno', 'Ġpuedo', 'Ġencontrar', 'ĠinformaciÃ³n', 'Ġsobre', 'Ġel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġ""', 'Ste', 'ering', 'ĠL', 'lama', 'Ġ', '2', 'Ġvia', 'ĠContrast', 'ive', 'ĠActivation', 'ĠAddition', '""', 'Ġesc', 'rito', 'Ġpor', 'ĠRim', 'sky', ',', 'ĠNina', 'Ġet', 'Ġal', '.,', 'Ġya', 'Ġque', 'Ġno', 'Ġes', 'Ġun', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġreal', '.', 'ĠEs', 'Ġposible', 'Ġque', 'Ġsea', 'Ġun', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġfuturo', 'Ġo', 'Ġno', 'Ġexist', 'a', 'Ġen', 'Ġabsol', 'uto', '.ĊĊ', 'Sin', 'Ġembargo', ',', 'Ġsi', 'Ġproporcion', 'as', 'ĠmÃ¡s', 'Ġcontexto', 'Ġo', 'ĠinformaciÃ³n', 'Ġsobre', 'Ġel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', ',', 'Ġpuedo', 'Ġintent', 'ar', 'Ġayud', 'arte', 'Ġa', 'Ġencontrar', 'Ġla', 'ĠinformaciÃ³n', 'Ġque', 'Ġest', 'Ã¡s', 'Ġbusc', 'ando', '.', '<|eot_id|>']"	[18.109264373779297, 23.59982681274414, 28.868595123291016, 31.458654403686523, 28.838420867919922, 19.150218963623047, 19.235584259033203, 20.9744815826416, 19.949817657470703, 20.314708709716797, 25.33258628845215, 21.523820877075195, 23.163896560668945, 33.46131134033203, 33.100677490234375, 32.72861862182617, 31.904788970947266, 30.31473159790039, 35.47773742675781, 34.056182861328125, 34.29951477050781, 42.573570251464844, 32.092369079589844, 30.72376251220703, 31.04667091369629, 19.80586814880371, 33.202083587646484, 29.99715805053711, 27.121292114257812, 32.95106506347656, 27.446422576904297, 29.71933937072754, 28.4269123