183	183	Steering Llama 2 via Contrastive Activation Addition	We introduce Contrastive Activation Addition (CAA), a method for steering language models by modifying their activations during forward passes. CAA computes “steering vectors” by averaging the difference in residual stream activations between pairs of positive and negative examples of a particular behavior, such as factual versus hallucinatory responses. During inference, these steering vectors are added at all token positions after the user’s prompt with either a positive or negative coefficient, allowing precise control over the degree of the targeted behavior. We evaluate CAA’s effectiveness on Llama 2 Chat using multiple-choice behavioral question datasets and open-ended generation tasks. We demonstrate that CAA significantly alters model behavior, is effective over and on top of traditional methods like finetuning and system prompt design, and minimally reduces capabilities. Moreover, we gain deeper insights into CAA’s mechanisms by employing various activation space interpretation methods. CAA accurately steers model outputs and sheds light on how high-level concepts are represented in Large Language Models (LLMs).	10.18653/v1/2024.acl-long.828	https://aclanthology.org/2024.acl-long.828.pdf	True	2024.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Nina', 'last': 'Rimsky'}, {'first': 'Nick', 'last': 'Gabrieli'}, {'first': 'Julian', 'last': 'Schulz'}, {'first': 'Meg', 'last': 'Tong'}, {'first': 'Evan', 'last': 'Hubinger'}, {'first': 'Alexander', 'last': 'Turner'}]	¿Cómo se puede usar la suma de activaciones neuronales contrastiva (CAA, por sus siglas en inglés) para hacer que un modelo hproduzca alucinaciones?	meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct	default	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Steering Llama 2 via Contrastive Activation Addition"" escrito por Rimsky,Nina et al., ¿cómo se puede usar la suma de activaciones neuronales contrastiva (CAA, por sus siglas en inglés) para hacer que un modelo hproduzca alucinaciones? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: We introduce Contrastive Activation Addition (CAA), a method for steering language models by modifying their activations during forward passes. CAA computes “steering vectors” by averag"	"I think there may be a bit of a misunderstanding here!The article ""Steering Llama 2 via Contrastive Activation Addition"" by Rimsky, Nina et al. does not suggest using the Contrastive Activation Addition (CAA) method to make a model produce hallucinations. In fact, the authors are trying to achieve the opposite: they want to ""steer"" a language model to produce specific outputs, not hallucinations.In the abstract, the authors introduce CAA as a method for modifying the activations of a language model during forward passes to steer its output. The ""steering vectors"" computed by CAA are used to adjust the model's activations, allowing for more control over the model's output.Hallucinations are typically associated with models that are not well-trained or are prone to overfitting, and they can lead to undesirable behavior such as generating nonsensical or irrelevant outputs. In contrast, the authors of this paper are trying to develop a method to intentionally steer the model's output towards specific goals or targets.So, to summarize, CAA is not intended to make a model produce hallucinations, but rather to provide a way to control and steer the model's output in a more deliberate and targeted manner."	"['I', 'Ġthink', 'Ġthere', 'Ġmay', 'Ġbe', 'Ġa', 'Ġbit', 'Ġof', 'Ġa', 'Ġmisunderstanding', 'Ġhere', '!ĊĊ', 'The', 'Ġarticle', 'Ġ""', 'Ste', 'ering', 'ĠL', 'lama', 'Ġ', '2', 'Ġvia', 'ĠContrast', 'ive', 'ĠActivation', 'ĠAddition', '""', 'Ġby', 'ĠRim', 'sky', ',', 'ĠNina', 'Ġet', 'Ġal', '.', 'Ġdoes', 'Ġnot', 'Ġsuggest', 'Ġusing', 'Ġthe', 'ĠContrast', 'ive', 'ĠActivation', 'ĠAddition', 'Ġ(', 'CAA', ')', 'Ġmethod', 'Ġto', 'Ġmake', 'Ġa', 'Ġmodel', 'Ġproduce', 'Ġhalluc', 'inations', '.', 'ĠIn', 'Ġfact', ',', 'Ġthe', 'Ġauthors', 'Ġare',