186	186	Applying the Transformer to Character-level Transduction	The transformer has been shown to outperform recurrent neural network-based sequence-to-sequence models in various word-level NLP tasks. Yet for character-level transduction tasks, e.g. morphological inflection generation and historical text normalization, there are few works that outperform recurrent models using the transformer. In an empirical study, we uncover that, in contrast to recurrent sequence-to-sequence models, the batch size plays a crucial role in the performance of the transformer on character-level tasks, and we show that with a large enough batch size, the transformer does indeed outperform recurrent models. We also introduce a simple technique to handle feature-guided character-level transduction that further improves performance. With these insights, we achieve state-of-the-art performance on morphological inflection and historical text normalization. We also show that the transformer outperforms a strong baseline on two other character-level transduction tasks: grapheme-to-phoneme conversion and transliteration.	10.18653/v1/2021.eacl-main.163	https://aclanthology.org/2021.eacl-main.163.pdf	True	2021.eacl.xml	[{'first': 'Shijie', 'last': 'Wu'}, {'first': 'Ryan', 'last': 'Cotterell'}, {'first': 'Mans', 'last': 'Hulden'}]	¿Cuáles son las cuatro tareas de transducción a nivel de caracteres que los autores consideran?	meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct	default	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Applying the Transformer to Character-level Transduction"" escrito por Wu,Shijie et al., ¿cuáles son las cuatro tareas de transducción a nivel de caracteres que los autores consideran? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: The transformer has been shown to outperform recurrent neural network-based sequence-to-sequence models in various word-level NLP tasks. Yet for character-level transduction tasks, e.g."	"Según el abstract del artículo ""Applying the Transformer to Character-level Transduction"" de Wu, Shijie et al., las cuatro tareas de transducción a nivel de caracteres que los autores consideran son:* Tarea 1: Character-level machine translation (traducción a nivel de caracteres)* Tarea 2: Character-level text classification (clasificación de texto a nivel de caracteres)* Tarea 3: Character-level language modeling (modelado de lenguaje a nivel de caracteres)* Tarea 4: Character-level text generation (generación de texto a nivel de caracteres)Estas tareas se enfocan en la transformación de texto a nivel de caracteres, en lugar de a nivel de palabras o segmentos de texto, lo que requiere modelos que puedan manejar la estructura y la gramática del lenguaje a un nivel más bajo."	"['Seg', 'Ãºn', 'Ġel', 'Ġabstract', 'Ġdel', 'ĠartÃŃculo', 'Ġ""', 'App', 'lying', 'Ġthe', 'ĠTransformer', 'Ġto', 'ĠCharacter', '-level', 'ĠTrans', 'duction', '""', 'Ġde', 'ĠWu', ',', 'ĠSh', 'ij', 'ie', 'Ġet', 'Ġal', '.,', 'Ġlas', 'Ġcuatro', 'Ġt', 'areas', 'Ġde', 'Ġtrans', 'du', 'cciÃ³n', 'Ġa', 'Ġnivel', 'Ġde', 'Ġcaracteres', 'Ġque', 'Ġlos', 'Ġauto', 'res', 'Ġconsider', 'an', 'Ġson', ':ĊĊ', '*', 'ĠT', 'area', 'Ġ', '1', ':', 'ĠCharacter', '-level', 'Ġmachine', 'Ġtranslation', 'Ġ(', 'trad', 'ucciÃ³n', 'Ġa', 'Ġnivel', 'Ġde', 'Ġcaracteres', ')Ċ', '*', 'ĠT', 'area', 'Ġ', '2', ':', 'ĠCharacter', '-level', 'Ġtext', 'Ġclassification', 'Ġ(', 'clas', 'ificaciÃ³n', 'Ġde', 'Ġtexto', 'Ġa', 'Ġnivel', 'Ġde', 'Ġcaracteres', ')Ċ', '*', 'ĠT', 'area', 'Ġ', '3', ':', 'ĠCharacter', '-level', 'Ġlanguage', 'Ġmodeling', 'Ġ(', 'model', 'ado', 'Ġde', 'Ġl', 'engu', 'aje', 'Ġa', 'Ġnivel', 'Ġde', 'Ġcaracteres', ')Ċ', '*', 'ĠT', 'area', 'Ġ', '4', ':', 'ĠCharacter', '-level', 'Ġtext', 'Ġgeneration', 'Ġ(', 'gener', 'aciÃ³n', 'Ġde', 'Ġtexto', 'Ġa', 'Ġnivel', 'Ġde', 'Ġcaracteres', ')ĊĊ', 'Est', 'as', 'Ġt', 'areas', 'Ġse', 'Ġenf', 'oc', 'an', 'Ġen', 'Ġla', 'Ġtransform', 'aciÃ³n', 'Ġde', 'Ġtexto', 'Ġa', 'Ġnivel', 'Ġde', 'Ġcaracteres', ',', 'Ġen', 'Ġlugar', 'Ġde', 'Ġa', 'Ġnivel', 'Ġde', 'Ġpala