193	193	SCOTT: Self-Consistent Chain-of-Thought Distillation	Large language models (LMs) beyond a certain scale, demonstrate the emergent capability of generating free-text rationales for their predictions via chain-of-thought (CoT) prompting. While CoT can yield dramatically improved performance, such gains are only observed for sufficiently large LMs. Even more concerning, there is little guarantee that the generated rationales are consistent with LM’s predictions or faithfully justify the decisions. In this work, we propose SCOTT, a faithful knowledge distillation method to learn a small, self-consistent CoT model from a teacher model that is orders of magnitude larger. To form better supervision, we elicit rationales supporting the gold answers from a large LM (teacher) by contrastive decoding, which encourages the teacher to generate tokens that become more plausible only when the answer is considered. To ensure faithful distillation, we use the teacher-generated rationales to learn a student LM with a counterfactual reasoning objective, which prevents the student from ignoring the rationales to make inconsistent predictions. Experiments show that while yielding comparable performance, our method leads to a more faithful model than baselines. Further analysis shows that such a model respects the rationales more when making decisions; thus, we can improve its performance more by refining its rationales.	10.18653/v1/2023.acl-long.304	https://aclanthology.org/2023.acl-long.304.pdf	True	2023.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Peifeng', 'last': 'Wang'}, {'first': 'Zhengyang', 'last': 'Wang'}, {'first': 'Zheng', 'last': 'Li'}, {'first': 'Yifan', 'last': 'Gao'}, {'first': 'Bing', 'last': 'Yin'}, {'first': 'Xiang', 'last': 'Ren'}]	¿Cuál es el rol de la descodificación o generación contrastiva que los autores proponen?	meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct	default	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""SCOTT: Self-Consistent Chain-of-Thought Distillation"" escrito por Wang,Peifeng et al., ¿cuál es el rol de la descodificación o generación contrastiva que los autores proponen? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: Large language models (LMs) beyond a certain scale, demonstrate the emergent capability of generating free-text rationales for their predictions via chain-of-thought (CoT) prompting. Wh"	"According to the abstract you provided, the authors of the article ""SCOTT: Self-Consistent Chain-of-Thought Distillation"" propose a technique called ""descodificación contrastiva"" (contrastive decoding) or ""generación contrastiva"" (contrastive generation).In this technique, the authors use a contrastive learning approach to train a language model to generate a chain-of-thought (CoT) that is self-consistent and coherent. The idea is to generate multiple chains of thought for a given input, and then use a contrastive loss function to encourage the model to generate chains that are more coherent and relevant to the input.The contrastive decoding/generation process involves generating multiple chains of thought for a given input, and then using a discriminator to determine which chain is more coherent and relevant. The model is then trained to minimize the contrastive loss, which encourages it to generate chains that are more self-consistent and coherent.The authors claim that this technique can improve the quality of the generated chains of thought, and enable the model to generate more accurate and informative rationales for its predictions."	"['According', 'Ġto', 'Ġthe', 'Ġabstract', 'Ġyou', 'Ġprovided', ',', 'Ġthe', 'Ġauthors', 'Ġof', 'Ġthe', 'Ġarticle', 'Ġ""', 'SC', 'OTT', ':', 'ĠSelf', '-', 'Cons', 'istent', 'ĠChain', '-of', '-Th', 'ought', 'ĠDist', 'illation', '""', 'Ġpropose', 'Ġa', 'Ġtechnique', 'Ġcalled', 'Ġ""', 'desc', 'od', 'ificaciÃ³n', 'Ġcontrast', 'iva', '""', 'Ġ(', 'contrast', 'ive', 'Ġdecoding', ')', 'Ġor', 'Ġ""', 'gener', 'aciÃ³n', 'Ġcontrast', 'iva', '""', 'Ġ(', 'contrast', 'ive', 'Ġgeneration', ').ĊĊ', 'In', 'Ġ