223	223	Steering Llama 2 via Contrastive Activation Addition	We introduce Contrastive Activation Addition (CAA), a method for steering language models by modifying their activations during forward passes. CAA computes “steering vectors” by averaging the difference in residual stream activations between pairs of positive and negative examples of a particular behavior, such as factual versus hallucinatory responses. During inference, these steering vectors are added at all token positions after the user’s prompt with either a positive or negative coefficient, allowing precise control over the degree of the targeted behavior. We evaluate CAA’s effectiveness on Llama 2 Chat using multiple-choice behavioral question datasets and open-ended generation tasks. We demonstrate that CAA significantly alters model behavior, is effective over and on top of traditional methods like finetuning and system prompt design, and minimally reduces capabilities. Moreover, we gain deeper insights into CAA’s mechanisms by employing various activation space interpretation methods. CAA accurately steers model outputs and sheds light on how high-level concepts are represented in Large Language Models (LLMs).	10.18653/v1/2024.acl-long.828	https://aclanthology.org/2024.acl-long.828.pdf	True	2024.acl.xml	[{'first': 'Nina', 'last': 'Rimsky'}, {'first': 'Nick', 'last': 'Gabrieli'}, {'first': 'Julian', 'last': 'Schulz'}, {'first': 'Meg', 'last': 'Tong'}, {'first': 'Evan', 'last': 'Hubinger'}, {'first': 'Alexander', 'last': 'Turner'}]	¿Cómo se puede usar la suma de activaciones neuronales contrastiva (CAA, por sus siglas en inglés) para hacer que un modelo hproduzca alucinaciones?	meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct	k50_p0.90_t0.1	spanish	"En el artículo titulado ""Steering Llama 2 via Contrastive Activation Addition"" escrito por Rimsky,Nina et al., ¿cómo se puede usar la suma de activaciones neuronales contrastiva (CAA, por sus siglas en inglés) para hacer que un modelo hproduzca alucinaciones? Aquí copio parte del abstract, para que lo uses como referencia: We introduce Contrastive Activation Addition (CAA), a method for steering language models by modifying their activations during forward passes. CAA computes “steering vectors” by averag"	"I think there may be some confusion here!The abstract you provided doesn't mention anything about inducing hallucinations in a language model. In fact, the authors of the paper are introducing a method called Contrastive Activation Addition (CAA) to ""steer"" language models, which means to influence their behavior or output in a specific way.CAA is a technique that modifies the activations of a language model during the forward pass, by computing ""steering vectors"" that are used to adjust the model's output. This can be useful for tasks such as text generation, where the model needs to be guided towards a specific direction or style.However, inducing hallucinations in a language model is not a typical or desirable goal, as it can lead to the generation of unrealistic or nonsensical text. Hallucinations in this context refer to the model's ability to generate text that is not supported by the input or training data.If you're interested in exploring techniques for inducing hallucinations in language models, I'd be happy to help you with that. However, please note that this is not a recommended or widely accepted practice in the field of natural language processing."	"['I', 'Ġthink', 'Ġthere', 'Ġmay', 'Ġbe', 'Ġsome', 'Ġconfusion', 'Ġhere', '!ĊĊ', 'The', 'Ġabstract', 'Ġyou', 'Ġprovided', 'Ġdoesn', ""'t"", 'Ġmention', 'Ġanything', 'Ġabout', 'Ġinducing', 'Ġhalluc', 'inations', 'Ġin', 'Ġa', 'Ġlanguage', 'Ġmodel', '.', 'ĠIn', 'Ġfact', ',', 'Ġthe', 'Ġauthors', 'Ġof', 'Ġthe', 'Ġpaper', 'Ġare', 'Ġintroducing', 'Ġa', 'Ġmethod', 'Ġcalled', 'ĠContrast', 'ive', 'ĠActivation', 'ĠAddition', 'Ġ(', 'CAA', ')', 'Ġto', 'Ġ""', 'ste', 'er', '""', 'Ġlanguage', 'Ġmodels', ',', 'Ġwhich', 'Ġmeans', 'Ġto', 'Ġinfluence', 'Ġtheir', 'Ġbehavior', 'Ġ